57.7	Martin_Amis	Martin Amis	Martin Louis Amis FRSL (* 25 August 1949 in Swansea, South Wales) is a British novelist, the author of many novels including Money (1984) and London Fields (1989). He was the Professor of Creative Writing at the Centre for New Writing at the University of Manchester, but stepped down at the end of the 2010/11 academic year. The Times named him in 2008 as one of the 50 greatest British writers since 1945.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9c/Martin_Amis_2012_by_Maximilian_Schoenherr.jpg/200px-Martin_Amis_2012_by_Maximilian_Schoenherr.jpg
